<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">'so that' needs to be followed with a full verb clause (subject + verb + object).</font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: ...of waves <font color="#0000ff"><b>to</b></font> generate...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">A relative pronoun which shows possession is needed here. 'The piston of the pump' in other words.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: ...the pump, <font color="#0000ff"><b>whose</b></font> piston...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: When <font color="#0000ff"><b>it</b></font> falls, ...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">'so that' needs to be followed with a full verb clause (subject + verb + object).<font face="verdana" size="12"/></font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: <font color="#0000ff"><b>Consequently</b></font>, the valve...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">'Due to' means 'because of'.<font face="verdana" size="12"/></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: <font color="#0000ff"><b>In order</b></font> to leave...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">'so that' needs to be followed with a full verb clause (subject + verb + object).<font face="verdana" size="12"/></font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: a turbine, <font color="#0000ff"><b>causing it</b></font> to rotate.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">'Who' is used to refer to people.<font face="verdana" size="12"/></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: ...to a generator, <font color="#0000ff"><b>which</b></font> converts...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: ...in this case <font color="#0000ff"><b>it</b></font> is surrounded...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p align="left">This is the second reference to the chamber, so 'a' is not appropriate here.<font face="verdana" size="12"/></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: ...another chamber, <font color="#0000ff"><b>which</b></font> is half...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">this</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb11">
  <p align="left">'So that' can't be used here because there is a comma.<font face="verdana" size="12"/></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: <font color="#0000ff"><b>As a result</b></font>, a current...</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb12">
  <p align="left">'Currents' is plural.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Correct: Due to <font color="#0000ff"><b>these</b></font> currents...</font>
  </p>
</section>

